    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI tried to move my config to 0.11 with the new deprecation of vim.fn.sign_define into vim.diagnostic.config.\nI am running into the issue that with the new way to configure the signs, signs are displaying on Linux but not on MacOS arm64.\nThe icons are not displaying with the new way to configure. I tried on 0.10.4 and 0.11 and the problem is the same on both. I am not sure if something is different with the MacOS configuration vs the Linux one since on Linux the signs are displaying correctly but on MacOS it only displays the first letter of the type (eg. W for warning).\n\nI am wondering if there is a way to check if the config is loading properly on Mac for that special `vim.diagnostic.config` because it seems to load fine on Linux.\n\nThanks for the help on that one!\n\nThis is the old way on MacOS:\n<img width=\"503\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/25530e11-11ed-4e1a-9637-46af5f1efbdb\" />\n\nThis is the new way on MacOS:\n<img width=\"554\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/952da7d7-5497-43a8-ad9f-1319e1a43798\" />\n\nThis is on Linux (old and new way to configure signs):\n<img width=\"268\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3d332f33-6c53-42c8-ae15-a51b0563c841\" />\n\n\nThis was the old config which is now raising warning:\n```\nlocal signs = { Error = \" \", Warn = \" \", Hint = \"ﴞ \", Info = \" \" }\nfor type, icon in pairs(signs) do\n        local hl = \"DiagnosticSign\" .. type\n        vim.fn.sign_define(hl, { text = icon, texthl = hl, numhl = \"\" })\nend\n```\nI moved it to:\n```\nvim.diagnostic.config({\n        signs = {\n                text = {\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.ERROR] = \" \",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.WARN] = \" \",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.INFO] = \"󰋼 \",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.HINT] = \"󰌵 \",\n                },\n                texthl = {\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.ERROR] = \"Error\",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.WARN] = \"Error\",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.HINT] = \"Hint\",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.INFO] = \"Info\",\n                },\n                numhl = {\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.ERROR] = \"\",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.WARN] = \"\",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.HINT] = \"\",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.INFO] = \"\",\n                },\n        },\n})\n```\n\nFull config is available [here](https://gitlab.com/loicdiridollou/configuration-files/-/blob/main/nvim/lua/plugins/lsp_config.lua?ref_type=heads).\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nConfigure the diagnostic with the config above on MacOS arm64.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIcons should display like the old behavior and not have the first letter for each severity.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nDid not try\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOs 15.3.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
