            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "`texthl` is an invalid key, just delete it. \n\nThis warning occues because we do not need to do `sign_define` for diagnostic signs, which should be placed in `vim.diagnostic.config({ signs = {}})`. texthl is done internally: `vim.diagnostic.severity.ERROR` use highligh group `DiagnosticSignError`, and `DiagnosticSignError` is link to `DiagnosticError` by default, same to WARN, INFO, HINT.\n\nBy the way, according to Screenshot, highlight is good.\n\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config({\n        signs = {\n                text = {\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.ERROR] = \" \",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.WARN] = \" \",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.INFO] = \"󰋼 \",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.HINT] = \"󰌵 \",\n                },\n                numhl = {\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.ERROR] = \"\",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.WARN] = \"\",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.HINT] = \"\",\n                        [vim.diagnostic.severity.INFO] = \"\",\n                },\n        },\n})\n```\n\nSign text is not correct on macos, try rebuild neovim in macos. make sure delete old runtime files. `/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/` before you do `make install`.",
